&lt;ol>
 

 &lt;li>Scoping potential funding for social work and social care research. This will involve producing a literature review for an expert group who will subsequently prepare a consultation document.&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Auditing the research capacity of UK social work educators. A survey will be undertaken of all social work academics in UK university departments that deliver qualifying training to identify the research qualifications, training, experience and networks of staff.&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Auditing research methods teaching in the new Social Work degree. A survey of all social work undergraduate qualifying courses will provide a map of the content and process of research teaching on the new degree in Social Work including attention to research across the curriculum.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;p>The results of the audit will inform ongoing deliberations about the developments and resources necessary to support building research capacity within the discipline of Social Work.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2008-05-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2007-10-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>37326</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/F033036/1</gtr:identifier><gtr:identifier type="RES">RES-068-25-0001</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>ACFABADE-E54A-4FC7-B9F5-259A19D97CDB</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Social Work</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>ACFABADE-E54A-4FC7-B9F5-259A19D97CDB</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Social Work</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic></gtr:researchTopics><gtr:rcukProgrammes/></gtr:project></gtr:projectComposition></gtr:projectOverview>